# HUMANTODO

Tasks that require human action. Once Symphony is running, create these as
Jira tickets in the PHONY project so agents can pick them up.

---

## Jira Setup (do this first)

Before creating tickets, you need a Jira project configured:
- Project key: PHONY
- Issue workflow states: Todo, In Progress, Blocked, In Review, Done, Cancelled
- Copy .env.example to .env and fill in JIRA_BASE_URL, JIRA_EMAIL, JIRA_API_TOKEN
- Fill in ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

---

## Symphony Implementation Tickets

Create each of the following as a Jira ticket in PHONY. Set them all to
"Todo" initially. Move to "In Progress" one at a time to dispatch to an agent.
Dependencies are noted — respect them when sequencing.

