### PHONY-6 — Workspace Manager + Hooks

**Description:**
Implement per-issue workspace creation, reuse, path safety invariants, and
lifecycle hook execution (spec Sections 9.1-9.5).

**Proposed Design:**
- src/workspace/workspaceManager.ts:
  - sanitizeIdentifier(id): replace all chars not in [A-Za-z0-9._-] with _
  - getWorkspacePath(identifier): <workspace.root>/<sanitized_identifier>
  - ensureWorkspace(identifier): create dir if missing (created_now=true),
    reuse if existing (created_now=false). Run after_create hook only when
    created_now=true. Return WorkspaceInfo.
  - removeWorkspace(identifier): run before_remove hook (best-effort), then
    rm -rf the directory.
- src/workspace/hookRunner.ts:
  - runHook(script, cwd, timeoutMs): spawn via "bash -lc <script>", enforce
    timeout with AbortController + setTimeout, return { ok, stdout, stderr }.
  - Log hook start, output (truncated), and any failures.
- Safety invariants (enforce before any agent launch):
  - workspace_path must be absolute
  - workspace_path must start with workspace_root + path.sep
  - Reject any path that fails this check with WorkspaceError("workspace_path_invalid")
- Hook failure semantics:
  - after_create failure: fatal, throw, workspace is considered uncreated
  - before_run failure: fatal, throw, abort the attempt
  - after_run failure: log and swallow
  - before_remove failure: log and swallow, cleanup proceeds

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Sanitization replaces all non-[A-Za-z0-9._-] chars with _
- after_create runs only on new directory creation, not on reuse
- before_run failure throws and prevents agent launch
- after_run failure is caught and logged, does not propagate
- Path traversal (../../etc) rejected by containment check
- Hook timeout kills the shell process
- Jest unit tests for all hook failure modes and safety invariants (spec 17.2)

**Dependencies:** PHONY-3, PHONY-7

