### PHONY-7 — Logging Infrastructure

**Description:**
Implement structured logging with three sinks: stderr, a complete log file,
and a grouped summary log file (spec Sections 13.1-13.2).

**Proposed Design:**
- src/logging/logger.ts: Logger class with methods debug/info/warn/error.
  Each accepts (message, context?) where context is a record of extra fields.
  Required context fields: issue_id, issue_identifier, session_id (all optional
  on the call site, attached via child loggers).
- createLogger(config): returns root Logger. Logger.child(context) returns a
  new Logger with merged context on every record.
- Log record shape: { level, timestamp (ISO), message, ...context }
- Sink 1 — stderr: formatted as "LEVEL timestamp message key=value key=value"
- Sink 2 — symphony.log: newline-delimited JSON, one record per line (complete)
- Sink 3 — symphony-summary.log: human-readable grouped summaries. Group by
  issue_identifier. Write a summary entry on: session start, each turn
  completion, session end (success/failure/retry), and errors. Format as:
  "[TIMESTAMP] [IDENTIFIER] EVENT: message"
- Log file paths from config (SYMPHONY_LOG_FILE, SYMPHONY_SUMMARY_LOG_FILE env
  vars, defaulting to ./symphony.log and ./symphony-summary.log)
- All sink writes wrapped in try/catch — sink failures must not throw

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- All three sinks receive output for each log call
- issue_id, issue_identifier, session_id flow through child loggers
- Sink failure does not propagate to caller
- Summary log has readable grouped-by-issue format (not raw JSON)
- Jest unit tests for formatting, context merging, and sink failure resilience

**Dependencies:** PHONY-1

