### PHONY-8 — Prompt Builder

**Description:**
Implement strict Liquid template rendering for per-issue prompts using the
WORKFLOW.md prompt body (spec Sections 5.4, 12.1-12.4).

**Proposed Design:**
- src/agent/promptBuilder.ts using the liquidjs package.
- buildPrompt(template, issue, attempt): string
  - Configure Liquid with strictVariables: true, strictFilters: true
  - Pass issue object (all fields) and attempt (null | number) as template vars
  - If template is empty string after trim, return default:
    "You are working on an issue from Jira."
  - Template parse error -> throw TemplateParseError
  - Render error (unknown var/filter) -> throw TemplateRenderError
- The issue object fields must be accessible as {{ issue.identifier }},
  {{ issue.title }}, {{ issue.description }}, {{ issue.state }}, etc.
- attempt is null on first run, an integer on retry/continuation

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- {{ issue.identifier }} renders correctly
- {{ attempt }} renders as null or integer
- Unknown variable throws TemplateRenderError (strict mode)
- Unknown filter throws TemplateRenderError
- Empty template body returns default prompt without error
- Jest unit tests covering all cases from spec 17.1

**Dependencies:** PHONY-3

