### PHONY-9 — Claude Agent Runner

**Description:**
Implement the agent runner using the Anthropic SDK, replacing the spec's
codex app-server stdio protocol with direct Claude API calls via tool use.
This is the execution core of Symphony (spec Section 10, adapted for Claude).

**Proposed Design:**
- src/agent/claudeRunner.ts: AgentRunner class
  - startSession(workspacePath, issue): sets up Anthropic client, tool handlers
  - runTurn(prompt, onEvent): calls anthropic.messages.create with streaming
    and tool_use, processes tool call loop, emits AgentEvent to onEvent callback
  - stopSession(): no-op for API-based runner (no subprocess to kill)
  - Model: claude-sonnet-4-6 (or latest available; make configurable)
- Tool definitions (all run with cwd = workspace path):
  - bash_execute(command): spawn via child_process.spawn("bash", ["-lc", command]),
    capture stdout+stderr, enforce timeout (default 60s per command).
    REJECT commands matching: /git\s+push\b.*\bmain\b/, /git\s+branch\s+-[Dd]\s+main/,
    /git\s+reset\b.*\bmain/, /git\s+checkout\s+-[Bb]\s+main/ when target is main.
    Return { stdout, stderr, exit_code }.
  - read_file(path): resolve path relative to workspace, read and return contents.
  - write_file(path, content): resolve path relative to workspace, write contents.
  - list_directory(path): resolve path relative to workspace, return entries.
- Event emission: map Anthropic streaming events to AgentEvent types:
  - message_start -> session_started
  - tool_use block -> approval_auto_approved (log tool name)
  - message_delta with stop_reason=end_turn -> turn_completed with usage
  - error -> turn_failed
  - tool result with is_error -> unsupported_tool_call or turn_ended_with_error
- Token tracking: extract usage from message_delta events, emit
  token_usage_updated events; track input/output/total.
- Timeouts: turn_timeout_ms enforced on the full runTurn call via AbortController.
- Trust posture: auto-approve all tool calls (no confirmation prompt).
  User-input-required -> not applicable for API mode; if agent produces no
  tool_use and no final response, treat as turn_input_required hard fail.
- Main branch protection: bash_execute rejects destructive-to-main patterns
  with a structured tool error response (does not crash the session).

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Agent can read/write files and run bash within workspace directory
- Relative paths resolved against workspace root, not process cwd
- Token counts emitted with each turn_completed event
- turn_timeout_ms kills the in-flight API call and returns turn_timeout error
- Main-branch-destructive bash commands rejected with tool error, session continues
- Tool call loop continues until stop_reason=end_turn or error
- Jest unit tests with mocked Anthropic client covering happy path, timeout,
  tool rejection, and error mapping

**Dependencies:** PHONY-6, PHONY-7, PHONY-8

