### PHONY-10 — Jira Tool Extension for Agent

**Description:**
Expose the Jira REST API as an agent tool so the coding agent can transition
issue states, add comments, and post PR links during its run. Analogous to the
spec's linear_graphql extension (spec Section 10.5, adapted for Jira REST).

**Proposed Design:**
- Add jira_api tool to Claude runner tool definitions when tracker.kind === "jira"
- Input schema:
  { method: "GET" | "POST" | "PUT", endpoint: string, body?: Record<string, unknown> }
  where endpoint is a Jira REST API v3 path (e.g. /rest/api/3/issue/PHONY-42/transitions)
- Validation: endpoint must be non-empty string, method must be GET/POST/PUT
- Execute: call Jira REST API using Symphony's configured auth (injected, never
  passed by the agent)
- Success: { success: true, data: <response body> }
- Jira API errors (non-2xx): { success: false, error: "<status>", data: <body> }
- Invalid input / missing auth / transport failure:
  { success: false, error: "<reason>" }
- Unsupported method or invalid input: return structured failure, session continues
- Auth must never appear in logs or tool responses

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Tool advertised in session startup
- Valid GET/POST/PUT calls execute against configured Jira instance
- Auth token never logged or included in tool response
- Non-2xx Jira response returns success=false while preserving body
- Invalid method returns structured failure without crashing session
- Jest unit tests with mocked Jira client

**Dependencies:** PHONY-5, PHONY-9

