### PHONY-11 — Orchestrator Core

**Description:**
Implement the central orchestrator: poll loop, dispatch, concurrency control,
reconciliation, retry queue, stall detection, and startup cleanup (spec
Sections 7-8, 16.1-16.6).

**Proposed Design:**
- src/orchestrator/orchestrator.ts: Orchestrator class owning
  OrchestratorRuntimeState. All state mutations happen synchronously in the
  Node.js event loop (no true threads). Use an async operation queue pattern
  to prevent races between poll ticks and worker exit callbacks.
- Poll loop: setTimeout-based. Respects dynamic poll_interval_ms changes.
  Immediate tick on startup (delay=0).
- Dispatch: shouldDispatch(issue, state) checks all eligibility rules from
  spec 8.2:
  - has id, identifier, title, state
  - state in active_states and not in terminal_states
  - not in running map
  - not in claimed set
  - global slots available: max(max_concurrent_agents - running.size, 0) > 0
  - per-state slots available (max_concurrent_agents_by_state lookup)
  - blocker rule: if state normalized === "todo", all blockers must be terminal
  Sort: priority asc (null last), then created_at asc, then identifier lex.
- Worker spawn: dispatch_issue() creates a Promise-based worker. Worker runs
  run_agent_attempt() which calls AgentRunner. Worker promise stored in
  RunningEntry.worker_promise.
- Worker exit: on_worker_exit() removes from running, updates codex_totals,
  schedules continuation retry (1000ms) on normal exit, exponential retry on
  failure.
- Retry backoff: delay = min(10000 * 2^(attempt-1), max_retry_backoff_ms)
  Continuation retry: fixed 1000ms delay, attempt=1.
- Reconciliation (every tick, before dispatch):
  Part A: stall detection — for each running issue, if elapsed since
  last_codex_timestamp (or started_at) > stall_timeout_ms, terminate + retry.
  Part B: fetch current states for all running issue IDs. Terminal -> terminate
  + cleanup workspace. Active -> update in-memory snapshot. Neither -> terminate,
  no cleanup. Fetch failure -> keep running, retry next tick.
- Startup terminal cleanup: fetch issues in terminal_states, remove their
  workspaces. Failure -> log warning, continue.
- Observer pattern: orchestrator.subscribe(listener: StateListener) for HTTP
  server and logging consumers.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- All dispatch eligibility rules from spec 8.2 enforced
- Sort order: priority asc -> oldest created -> identifier lex
- Backoff formula: min(10000 * 2^(attempt-1), max_retry_backoff_ms)
- Continuation retry uses 1000ms fixed delay, attempt=1
- Stall detection kills worker and queues retry
- Terminal tracker state -> terminate + workspace cleanup
- Non-active (not terminal) tracker state -> terminate, no cleanup
- Reconciliation state-refresh failure keeps workers running
- Global and per-state concurrency limits enforced
- Jest unit tests covering all cases from spec 17.4

**Dependencies:** PHONY-4, PHONY-5, PHONY-6, PHONY-7, PHONY-9

